msdpMIB.name: msdpMIB

msdpMIB.description: An experimental MIB module for MSDP Management.

msdpEnabled.name: msdpEnabled
msdpEnabled.description: The state of MSDP on this MSDP speaker - globally enabled or disabled.

msdpCacheLifetime.name: msdpCacheLifetime
msdpCacheLifetime.description: The lifetime given to SA cache entries when created or refreshed. A value of 0 means no SA caching is done by this MSDP speaker.

msdpNumSACacheEntries.name: msdpNumSACacheEntries
msdpNumSACacheEntries.description: The total number of entries in the SA Cache table.

msdpSAHoldDownPeriod.name: msdpSAHoldDownPeriod
msdpSAHoldDownPeriod.description: The number of seconds in the MSDP SA Hold-down period

msdpRequestsTable.name: msdpRequestsTable
msdpRequestsTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing group ranges and MSDP peers used when deciding where to send an SA Request message when required. If SA Caching is enabled, this table may be empty.

msdpRequestsEntry.name: msdpRequestsEntry
msdpRequestsEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing a group range used when deciding where to send an SA Request message.

msdpRequestsGroupAddress.name: msdpRequestsGroupAddress
msdpRequestsGroupAddress.description: The group address that, when combined with the mask in this entry, represents the group range for which this peer will service MSDP SA Requests.

msdpRequestsGroupMask.name: msdpRequestsGroupMask
msdpRequestsGroupMask.description: The mask that, when combined with the group address in this entry, represents the group range for which this peer will service MSDP SA Requests.

msdpRequestsPeer.name: msdpRequestsPeer
msdpRequestsPeer.description: The peer to which MSDP SA Requests for groups matching this entry's group range will be sent. Must match the INDEX of a row in the msdpPeerTable.

msdpRequestsStatus.name: msdpRequestsStatus
msdpRequestsStatus.description: The status of this row, by which new rows may be added to the table.

msdpPeerTable.name: msdpPeerTable
msdpPeerTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the MSDP speaker's peers.

msdpPeerEntry.name: msdpPeerEntry
msdpPeerEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing an MSDP peer.

msdpPeerRemoteAddress.name: msdpPeerRemoteAddress
msdpPeerRemoteAddress.description: The address of the remote MSDP peer.

msdpPeerState.name: msdpPeerState
msdpPeerState.description: The state of the MSDP TCP connection with this peer.

msdpPeerRPFFailures.name: msdpPeerRPFFailures
msdpPeerRPFFailures.description: The number of RPF failures on SA messages received from this peer.

msdpPeerInSAs.name: msdpPeerInSAs
msdpPeerInSAs.description: The number of MSDP SA messages received on this connection. This object should be initialized to zero when the connection is established.

msdpPeerOutSAs.name: msdpPeerOutSAs
msdpPeerOutSAs.description: The number of MSDP SA messages transmitted on this connection. This object should be initialized to zero when the connection is established.

msdpPeerInSARequests.name: msdpPeerInSARequests
msdpPeerInSARequests.description: The number of MSDP SA-Request messages received on this connection. This object should be initialized to zero when the connection is established.

msdpPeerOutSARequests.name: msdpPeerOutSARequests
msdpPeerOutSARequests.description: The number of MSDP SA-Request messages transmitted on this connection. This object should be initialized to zero when the connection is established.

msdpPeerInSAResponses.name: msdpPeerInSAResponses
msdpPeerInSAResponses.description: The number of MSDP SA-Response messages received on this connection. This object should be initialized to zero when the connection is established.

msdpPeerOutSAResponses.name: msdpPeerOutSAResponses
msdpPeerOutSAResponses.description: The number of MSDP SA Response messages transmitted on this TCP connection. This object should be initialized to zero when the connection is established.

msdpPeerInControlMessages.name: msdpPeerInControlMessages
msdpPeerInControlMessages.description: The total number of MSDP messages received on this TCP connection. This object should be initialized to zero when the connection is established.

msdpPeerOutControlMessages.name: msdpPeerOutControlMessages
msdpPeerOutControlMessages.description: The total number of MSDP messages transmitted on this TCP connection. This object should be initialized to zero when the connection is established.

msdpPeerInDataPackets.name: msdpPeerInDataPackets
msdpPeerInDataPackets.description: The total number of encapsulated data packets received from this peer. This object should be initialized to zero when the connection is established.

msdpPeerOutDataPackets.name: msdpPeerOutDataPackets
msdpPeerOutDataPackets.description: The total number of encapsulated data packets sent to this peer. This object should be initialized to zero when the connection is established.

msdpPeerFsmEstablishedTransitions.name: msdpPeerFsmEstablishedTransitions
msdpPeerFsmEstablishedTransitions.description: The total number of times the MSDP FSM transitioned into the established state.

msdpPeerFsmEstablishedTime.name: msdpPeerFsmEstablishedTime
msdpPeerFsmEstablishedTime.description: This timer indicates how long (in seconds) this peer has been in the Established state or how long since this peer was last in the Established state. It is set to zero when a new peer is configured or the MSDP speaker is booted.

msdpPeerInMessageElapsedTime.name: msdpPeerInMessageElapsedTime
msdpPeerInMessageElapsedTime.description: Elapsed time in seconds since the last MSDP message was received from the peer. Each time msdpPeerInControlMessages is incremented, the value of this object is set to zero (0).

msdpPeerLocalAddress.name: msdpPeerLocalAddress
msdpPeerLocalAddress.description: The local IP address of this entry's MSDP connection.

msdpPeerSAAdvPeriod.name: msdpPeerSAAdvPeriod
msdpPeerSAAdvPeriod.description: Time interval in seconds for the MinSAAdvertisementInterval MSDP timer.

msdpPeerConnectRetryInterval.name: msdpPeerConnectRetryInterval
msdpPeerConnectRetryInterval.description: Time interval in seconds for the ConnectRetry timer.

msdpPeerHoldTimeConfigured.name: msdpPeerHoldTimeConfigured
msdpPeerHoldTimeConfigured.description: Time interval in seconds for the Hold Timer configured for this MSDP speaker with this peer.

msdpPeerKeepAliveConfigured.name: msdpPeerKeepAliveConfigured
msdpPeerKeepAliveConfigured.description: Time interval in seconds for the KeepAlive timer configured for this MSDP speaker with this peer. A reasonable maximum value for this timer would be configured to be one third of that of msdpPeerHoldTimeConfigured. If the value of this object is zero (0), no periodic KEEPALIVE messages are sent to the peer after the MSDP connection has been established.

msdpPeerDataTtl.name: msdpPeerDataTtl
msdpPeerDataTtl.description: The minimum TTL a packet is required to have before it may be forwarded using SA encapsulation to this peer.

msdpPeerProcessRequestsFrom.name: msdpPeerProcessRequestsFrom
msdpPeerProcessRequestsFrom.description: This object indicates whether or not to process MSDP SA Request messages from this peer. If True(1), MSDP SA Request messages from this peer are processed and replied to (if appropriate) with SA Response messages. If False(2), MSDP SA Request messages from this peer are silently ignored. It defaults to False when msdpCacheLifetime is 0 and True when msdpCacheLifetime is non-0.

msdpPeerStatus.name: msdpPeerStatus
msdpPeerStatus.description: The RowStatus object by which peers can be added and deleted. A transition to 'active' will cause the MSDP Start Event to be generated. A transition out of the 'active' state will cause the MSDP Stop Event to be generated. Care should be used in providing write access to this object without adequate authentication.

msdpPeerRemotePort.name: msdpPeerRemotePort
msdpPeerRemotePort.description: The remote port for the TCP connection between the MSDP peers.

msdpPeerLocalPort.name: msdpPeerLocalPort
msdpPeerLocalPort.description: The local port for the TCP connection between the MSDP peers.

msdpPeerEncapsulationState.name: msdpPeerEncapsulationState
msdpPeerEncapsulationState.description: The status of the encapsulation negotiation state machine.

msdpPeerEncapsulationType.name: msdpPeerEncapsulationType
msdpPeerEncapsulationType.description: The encapsulation in use when encapsulating data in SA messages to this peer.

msdpPeerConnectionAttempts.name: msdpPeerConnectionAttempts
msdpPeerConnectionAttempts.description: The number of times the state machine has transitioned from inactive to connecting.

msdpPeerInNotifications.name: msdpPeerInNotifications
msdpPeerInNotifications.description: The number of MSDP Notification messages received on this connection. This object should be initialized to zero when the connection is established.

msdpPeerOutNotifications.name: msdpPeerOutNotifications
msdpPeerOutNotifications.description: The number of MSDP Notification messages transmitted on this connection. This object should be initialized to zero when the connection is established.

msdpPeerLastError.name: msdpPeerLastError
msdpPeerLastError.description: The last error code and subcode seen by this peer on this connection. If no error has occurred, this field is zero. Otherwise, the first byte of this two byte OCTET STRING contains the error code, and the second byte contains the subcode.

msdpSACacheTable.name: msdpSACacheTable
msdpSACacheTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the MSDP SA advertisements currently in the MSDP speaker's cache.

msdpSACacheEntry.name: msdpSACacheEntry
msdpSACacheEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing an MSDP SA advert.

msdpSACacheGroupAddr.name: msdpSACacheGroupAddr
msdpSACacheGroupAddr.description: The group address of the SA Cache entry.

msdpSACacheSourceAddr.name: msdpSACacheSourceAddr
msdpSACacheSourceAddr.description: The source address of the SA Cache entry.

msdpSACacheOriginRP.name: msdpSACacheOriginRP
msdpSACacheOriginRP.description: The address of the RP which originated the last SA message accepted for this entry.

msdpSACachePeerLearnedFrom.name: msdpSACachePeerLearnedFrom
msdpSACachePeerLearnedFrom.description: The peer from which this SA Cache entry was last accepted. This address must correspond to the msdpPeerRemoteAddress value for a row in the MSDP Peer Table.

msdpSACacheRPFPeer.name: msdpSACacheRPFPeer
msdpSACacheRPFPeer.description: The peer from which an SA message corresponding to this cache entry would be accepted (i.e. the RPF peer for msdpSACacheOriginRP). This may be different than msdpSACachePeerLearnedFrom if this entry was created by an MSDP SA-Response. This address must correspond to the msdpPeerRemoteAddress value for a row in the MSDP Peer Table.

msdpSACacheInSAs.name: msdpSACacheInSAs
msdpSACacheInSAs.description: The number of MSDP SA messages received relevant to this cache entry. This object must be initialized to zero when creating a cache entry.

msdpSACacheInDataPackets.name: msdpSACacheInDataPackets
msdpSACacheInDataPackets.description: The number of MSDP encapsulated data packets received relevant to this cache entry. This object must be initialized to zero when creating a cache entry.

msdpSACacheUpTime.name: msdpSACacheUpTime
msdpSACacheUpTime.description: The time since this entry was placed in the SA cache.

msdpSACacheExpiryTime.name: msdpSACacheExpiryTime
msdpSACacheExpiryTime.description: The time remaining before this entry will expire from the SA cache.

msdpSACacheStatus.name: msdpSACacheStatus
msdpSACacheStatus.description: The status of this row in the table. The only allowable actions are to retreive the status, which will be `active', or to set the status to `destroy' in order to remove this entry from the cache.

msdpEstablished.name: msdpEstablished
msdpEstablished.description: The MSDP Established event is generated when the MSDP FSM enters the ESTABLISHED state.

msdpBackwardTransition.name: msdpBackwardTransition
msdpBackwardTransition.description: The MSDPBackwardTransition Event is generated when the MSDP FSM moves from a higher numbered state to a lower numbered state.

msdpMIBCompliance.name: msdpMIBCompliance
msdpMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the MSDP MIB.

msdpMIBGlobalsGroup.name: msdpMIBGlobalsGroup
msdpMIBGlobalsGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information on global MSDP state.

msdpMIBPeerGroup.name: msdpMIBPeerGroup
msdpMIBPeerGroup.description: A collection of objects for managing MSDP peers.

msdpSACacheGroup.name: msdpSACacheGroup
msdpSACacheGroup.description: A collection of objects for managing MSDP SA cache entries.
